Sentencas: Dense doped ceria films are promising candidate electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated at intermediate temperature (similar to 500 degrees C).

Sentencas: In this work, detailed microstructural features of Gd-doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte film supported by Ni-GDC cermet anode were studied.

Sentencas: Formation of inhomogeneous microstructures in the GDC film was observed, which was enhanced in the region near the film/anode interface due to the Ni diffusion from the anode.
